{
  "doc_id": "38153",
  "text": "When originally cloned, GITR was found upregulated in a hybridoma T cell line treated with glucocorticoids [CITATION_1] . GITR is, however, only slightly upregulated in T cells in primary cultures treated with glucocorticoids [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] , and in Treg cells after dexamethasone treatment [CITATION_4] . GITR expression in T cells is not decreased in glucocorticoid receptor knock out mice [CITATION_5] and, in humans, is not upregulated in T cells after glucocorticoid treatment [CITATION_6] [CITATION_7] . Therefore, the relationship between GITR and glucocorticoids remains controversial and seems to have slight functional meaning, if any.",
